<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407084>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 6. Pseudoodes coelestinus Chaudoir, 1882 (A–C: Oodes coelestinus, holotype; D–E: Oodes viridissimus, holotype; F–G: female specimen, Malaysia, Long Láma). A, D: habitus and labels; B: left metepisternum and metacoxa (arrow shows lateral end of metacoxal basal sulcus); C: right mesotarsomeres; E: head and pronotum; F: mentum; G: prosternal process. Scale lines = 2 mm (Fig. A, D); = 1 mm (Figs B–C, E); = 0.5 mm (Figs F–G)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4407084/files/figure.png" .

